KAROO - There has been some relief for the drought-stricken Karoo. Videos posted on social media show a flowing river, after significant rainfall this week. Samara Game Reserve in the Eastern Cape calls the rain glorious and says it's grateful. READ:Â Karoo residents experience worst drought in more than a century The Karoo has been suffering drought, leaving farmers and residents devastated. It will need more rain to mitigate the impact of the dry spell.